The paper discusses the implementation of deconvolutional neural networks (DCNNs) for computer vision applications, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and augmented reality (cs.AR) sub-categories. The use of FPGA accelerators also suggests a potential fit for the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also discusses the optimization of the design, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
